{
  "texts": [
    "We apply the language consistency reward to both reasoning and non-reasoning data by directly adding it to the final reward.",
    "Note that the clip ratio plays a crucial role in training.",
    "A lower value can lead to the truncation of gradients for a large number of tokens, thereby degrading the performance of the model, whereas a higher value may cause instability during training.",
    "Details of RL data used in this stage are provided in Supplementary Information, section 2.3.",
    "Training details of the second RL stage."
  ]
}